Step: Command

aggregate.label:
Step: Aggregate
- list of dependencies -> used in business rules along with data from command
- business rules -> define how to handle command, event recording conditions

event.label:
Step: Event
- schema -> Event contract
- apply rules -> How event information should be applied to state

document.label:
Step: State
- namespace -> groups related information e.g. State + State List
- identifier -> What property identifies the state e.g. Employee Id
- schema -> How is the state structured? Used to display state in FE
- uiSchema -> Styling of view component used to display state in FE

UserObject.label:
Events are at the core!

Read our philosophy

<font style="font-size: 24px;" color="#ffffff"> Collaborate across boundaries using Big Picture Event Storming. Events are everywhere. Use them to explore opportunities, identify pain points and discuss user needs </font>

Design detailed solutions w/out leaving the collaboration space. We call it Continuous Event Storming and it's some kind of Visual-Mob-Programming.
Cody Wizard is a design-assistance-tool integrated on prooph board. 
It will guide you through the design process.

prooph board is the central collaboration hub. Here goals are set, socio-technical architecture is discussed, tasks are defined and features designed. 
The design – aka Event Map – serves as a software blueprint as well as documentation. 
Cody makes sure that both are kept in sync.
Cody is an Open Source code generation bot. It understands Event Maps and can turn them into prototypes, MVPs and even fully working web applications.

Cody Engine is an Open Source prototyping and web application framework. On the one hand it has all "batteries included" and on the other hand it is still highly customizable. 
One coherent client-server-stack based on TypeScript, Node.js, React and Material UI. It emphasizes Task-based UIs and leverages the power of Event Sourcing and Event-Driven Architecture to guarantee a first-class result.

Events are at the core!
